Package: drmTMB
Title: Distributional Regression Models Using 'TMB'
Version: 0.2.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Shinichi", "Nakagawa", email = "itchyshin@gmail.com",
           role = c("aut", "cre", "cph"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-7765-5182"))
  )
Description: Fit distributional regression models for univariate and
    bivariate responses using 'Template Model Builder' ('TMB'). Predictors can
    model location, scale, shape, zero-inflation, hurdle probability,
    random-effect scale, and bivariate residual correlation. Supported
    families include Gaussian, Student-t, positive-continuous, Tweedie
    semicontinuous, bounded-proportion, count, ordinal cumulative-logit, and
    Gaussian meta-analytic known-covariance models. The package is designed for
    applied ecology, evolution, and environmental-science analyses that need
    model diagnostics and explicit boundaries between fitted and planned syntax.
